description.narrative:
As a marginalized group in society, there are various needs for former prisoners to reintegrate into society following their release, including jobs, psychological help, health care, etc. Compared to male former inmates, female counterparts are more likely in dilemma and dire need of support.

 Legal aid is amongst the top specific needs for ex-prisoners in post-release. This is echoed in many international documents such as the United Nations Standard Minimum Rules for Non-custodial Measures (the Tokyo Rules), United Nations Rules for the Treatment of Women Prisoners and Non-custodial Measures for Women Offenders.

 In Vietnam, the Government issued Decree No. 80/2011/N#-CP on measures to ensure community integration for persons having completely served their prison sentences (Decree 80) and recently issued Decree No. 49/2020 guiding Law on Criminal Execution, replacing Decree 80 as of 15th June 2020. These documents demonstrate the concern of the Vietnamese Government on social integration for prisoners in post-release.

 As the most populated city in Vietnam, Ho Chi Minh City is home to many ex-prisoners. Through the surveying practice, it can be seen that there have not been many effective programmes supporting ex-prisoners and no programme supporting specifically female ex-prisoners in Vietnam, let alone legal support programmes. Therefore, Ho Chi Minh University of Law proposed to implement Program #Raising awareness and providing legal support on labour, employment and related issues for women who have served their sentences in HCMC#, which is to address the five following issues:
 1. Building awareness for female ex-prisoners about labour laws to protect them at work;
 2. Addressing legal issues related to seeking jobs and community reintegration of female ex-prisoners;
 3. Unifying contents and procedures in  administration on female ex-prisoners;
 4. Improving relevant policies and laws;
 5. Reducing the likelihood of returning to crime among female ex-prisoners to ensure social security.
